The paper discusses operations for refining and coarsening state spaces in Bayesian Networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning applications. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses practical implications for knowledge acquisition, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper deals with uncertainty and probability, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
